ion",EducationLevel:"education level"},Po={value:window.RDL.Localization.resumePreviewAddLater_Text||""},Io={SKIP:["CTP2","RBN1","CNT2"],"STUD-Y":["MDL1","CNT2","CTP2"],"STUD-N":["LCB4","RBN1","CNT2"],MIDLEVEL:["RBN1","MLU2","CTP2"],EXPLEVEL:["CNT2","HDR3","CTP2"],GROUP1:["SLI2","CTP2","CNT4"],GROUP2:["MLU2","CNT4","CTP2"],GROUP3:["HDR3","CNT2","RBN1"]},_o={freeform_heading:window.RDL.Localization.freeform_heading||"Add any additional coursework you're proud to showcase",freeform_tips_title:window.RDL.Localization.freeform_tips_title||"Look here for sample resume references",pro_tip_title:window.RDL.Localization.pro_tip_title||"Pro Tip",pro_tip_desc:window.RDL.Localization.pro_tip_desc,placeholder_text_educ:window.RDL.Localization.placeholder_text_educ,editor_label:window.RDL.Localization.editor_label,ttc_label:window.RDL.Localization.ttc_label||"Our Recommendations",sample_tips:{heading:window.RDL.Localization.sample_tips_heading||"Education Section Samples",sample_tag:window.RDL.Localization.sample_tips_tag||"Sample",sample_1:{para_1:{title:"XYZ College",sub_title:"May 2021",data:{data_1:"Bachelor of Arts in English, department honors",data_2:"3.8 GPA"}}},sample_2:{para_1:{title:"EDUCATION",sub_title:"XYZ College",data:{data_1:"Bachelor of Arts in English, department honors"}},para_2:{title:"Awards and Honors",data:{data_1:"Summa cum laude",data_2:"ABC Award for outstanding journalism major"}}}},pro_tip_copy:window.RDL.Localization.pro_tip_copy||{NoExpLevel:{Yes:{HighSchool:"No work experience yet? Here's a tip. <br />Make this a coursework-focused resume instead. Include AP classes, college coursework, honors & awards, a GPA (3.5 or higher), or any extracurricular activities.",Associates:"No work experience yet? We suggest making this a coursework-focused resume instead. Use this section to include relevant coursework even if it's in-progress, a GPA (3.5 or higher), scholarships or any other certification that highlights your skills for the job you want.",Bachelors:"As a Bachelor's student, you can focus this section on the no. of credits completed so far, extracurricular activities, scholarships or any honors & awards received.",Masters:"As a Master's student or someone taking on higher education, we suggest including relevant project experience (thesis, capstone project, etc.) or any international studies undertaken. If you've received a scholarship, or undergone training to develop a skill for a job, you can add it here too.",College:"No work experience yet? We've got you. Use this section to highlight relevant education for the job you want. Include coursework (even if it's in-progress), semester hours completed, or any certification received.",Vocational:"Showcase your vocational experience through coursework, apprenticeships and scholarships that are relevant to the job you want. You could even use relevant keywords from the job description to relate it to your education."},No:{HighSchool:"No work experience yet? Here's our suggestion. Make it a coursework-focused resume instead. In this section, you can include AP classes, honors & awards, a GPA (3.5 or higher) or extracurricular activities & memberships.",Associates:"No work experience yet? We've got you. Include relevant coursework, honors & awards or any scholarship that showcases your skills for the job you want. ",Bachelors:"No work experience yet? Here's our suggestion - include the no. of credits completed in your Bachelor's degree, any student organizations you were a part of, or even any extra-curricular activities you participated in.",Masters:"If you are a Master's student or someone taking on higher education, use this section to highlight relevant project experience (thesis, a capstone project) or any international studies undertaken.",College:"No work experience yet? Here's a tip - use this section to include relevant coursework, apprenticeships or any certification that showcases your skills for the job you want.",Vocational:"Showcase your vocational experience through relevant coursework, apprenticeships and certifications that correspond to the job you want. You could even use relevant keywords from the job description to relate it to your education."}},EntryLevel:{Yes:{HighSchool:"We suggest having a coursework-focused resume for high school students. Include AP classes, extra-curricular activities, a GPA (3.5 or higher), or any certification that highlights your professional development.",Associates:"Since you have an associate degree, why not include honors & awards, scholarships or any training that highlights your professional development? We recommend adding the most relevant coursework, even if it is in-progress.",Bachelors:"As a Bachelor's student, we recommend adding relevant coursework, the no. of credits completed so far, extracurricular activities, and scholarships received. Include any training related to your professional development too.",Masters:"As a Master's student or someone taking on higher education, we suggest including your thesis, capstone project or any relevant project experience here. If you've received a scholarship, or undergone training to develop a skill for a job, you can add it here too.",College:"Why not include job-related coursework or training that highlights your professional development? We recommend adding the most noteworthy ones, even if they are in-progress!",Vocational:"Showcase your vocational experience through coursework, apprenticeships and scholarships that are relevant to the job you want. You could even use relevant keywords from the job description to relate it to your education."},No:{HighSchool:"We recommend adding this section if you have under 3 years of work experience. Add a school specialization, an honors designation, a GPA (3.5 or higher), or relevant coursework that emphasizes your skills.",Associates:"We recommend adding this section if you have under 3 years of work experience. <br />If you are a recent graduate, include your degree, a GPA (3.5 or higher), any honors and awards, scholarships or even relevant coursework that showcases your skills for the job you want.",Bachelors:"Since you have a Bachelor's degree, we recommend adding your major area of study, extracurricular activities, dean's list accolades, or even a GPA of above 3.5 (if required by the job application). Any education completed in the last 2 years that can show your value to the employer is a plus.",Masters:"Since you have a Master's degree, we suggest including your thesis, capstone project or any other relevant project experience here. If you've received a scholarship, or undergone training to develop a skill for a job, you can add it here too. Any coursework that shows your value to the employer is a plus.",College:"We recommend adding this section if you have under 3 years of work experience. <br />Include any relevant coursework, a major area of study, or even an apprenticeship experience that showcases your skills for the job you want. ",Vocational:"This section can help you stand out. Showcase your vocational experience through coursework, scholarships or grants received or even projects that are relevant to the job you want. Any education that showcases your skills is a plus."}},MidLevel:{HighSchool:"Any coursework undertaken for your professional development can be added here. To showcase your best work to employers, we suggest including the most relevant ones first.",Associates:"This section can make you stand apart from other candidates. Include relevant coursework, honors & awards, a GPA (3.5 or higher), or even certifications that highlight your skills for the job you want.",Bachelors:"If you've graduated with Honors or undertaken any coursework relevant to the job you want, add it here in chronological order. Other education completed within the last 2 years of graduating can be included here as well.",Masters:"We suggest adding a thesis, dissertation or relevant projects undertaken. If you've graduated with Honors, you can include that too. <br />Shortlist the ones that best support the job you want, and add it here in chronological order.",College:"This section can make you stand apart from other candidates. Include relevant coursework, a major area of study, or even an apprenticeship experience that highlights your skills for the job you want.",Vocational:"This section can help you stand out. You may include an apprenticeship experience, a relevant certification, or even a major area of study. Any education that showcases your skills for the job you want is a plus."}},addTTCbtn:window.RDL.Localization.educAddTTCbtn||""},xo={pro_ttc:[{h1:window.RDL.Localization.proTTCContentHeading||"Awards and Recognition",h2:window.RDL.Localization.proTTCContentSubHeading||"Add details to support your achievements.",ttc:[{title:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcTitle||"Award or Honor",ttc:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcSubtitle||"[Award] Recipient"},{title:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcTitle_1||"Dean's List",ttc:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcSubtitle_1||"[Semester, Year] - Dean's List"},{title:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcTitle_2||"Honor Roll",ttc:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcSubtitle_2||"[Semester, Year] - Honor Roll"}]},{h1:window.RDL.Localization.proTTCContentHeading_1||"Scholarships and Grants",h2:window.RDL.Localization.proTTCContentSubHeading_1||"It takes hard work to be awarded one of these - you should shine a light on that!",ttc:[{title:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcTitle_3||"Discretionary or Competitive Grant",ttc:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcSubtitle_3||"Awarded [Grant Name], [Agency Name]"},{title:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcTitle_4||"Scholarship",ttc:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcSubtitle_4||"[Scholarship Name] Recipient"}]},{h1:window.RDL.Localization.proTTCContentHeading_2||"Coursework",h2:window.RDL.Localization.proTTCContentSubHeading_2||"Have you completed additional studies that are beneficial to the job you're applying for?",ttc:[{title:window.RDL.Localization.proTTcTitle_5||"Adv